BIB                 13         25
TITLE      Neutron transfer in the 48Ca + 197Au reaction
AUTHOR     (A.K.Azhibekov,S.M.Lukyanov,A.V.Shakhov,
           Yu.E.Penionzhkevich,M.A.Naumenko,H.M.Devaraja,
           E.K.Almanbetova,B.A.Urazbekov,A.Yu.Bodrov,
           E.V.Mardyban,A.Bahini,K.Mendibayev)
INSTITUTE  (4ZZZDUB,4RUSMIF,4KASKAZ,4KASATN,3SAFITH)
           (4KASKAS) Korkyt Ata Kyzylorda University, Kyzylorda
REFERENCE  (J,EPJ/A,59,278,2023)
           #doi:10.1140/epja/s10050-023-01192-4
FACILITY   (ISOCY,4ZZZDUB) U400-M
INC-SOURCE The beam current was approximately 50 nA.
SAMPLE     Three 197Au targets, each with a thickness of 2 mu-m.
DETECTOR   (HPGE) Canberra spectrometer based on an HPGe(Li)
           crystal with a high FWHM resolution of 1.5-2 keV and a
           photopeak efficiency of approximately 10%.
METHOD     (ACTIV,GSPEC,TOF,BCINT)
ANALYSIS   (DECAY)
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) The statistical errors for the cross
           sections were determined as the root mean square of
           errors across all measurements. Additionally, each
           measurements error comprises the statistical error of
           the extracted photopeak area and the errors arising
           from detector efficiency.
STATUS     (CURVE,,A.K.Azhibekov+,J,EPJ/A,59,278,2023) Fig. 4
HISTORY    (20260121C)
